excerpt: Brand museum for Philips' products & developments in music, lighting, health & communications.
detail_description: The Philips Museum in Eindhoven is a brand museum showcasing the products and developments of Philips in various fields such as music, lighting, health, and communications. The museum offers insights into the impact of Philips on the urban development of Eindhoven, transforming it from a small market town to a vibrant city with new industrial zones and working-class districts. It provides visitors with an appreciation of how Philips has shaped the city's landscape.
name: Philips Museum

excerpt: Contemporary & experimental art, installations & photo exhibitions in a sleek, modern museum.
detail_description: Located in the Stratumseind district of Eindhoven, the Van Abbemuseum is a renowned institution for modern and contemporary art. Since its establishment in 1936, it has undergone significant renovations, including a futuristic extension surrounded by a moat. The museum's extensive collection features works by prominent artists such as Picasso, Mondrian, Chagall, and El Lissitzky. Visitors can explore a diverse range of contemporary art from both Dutch and international artists through ever-changing temporary exhibitions.
name: Van Abbemuseum

excerpt: Museum telling the story of the DAF brand, displaying trucks & rare production & prototype vehicles.
detail_description: The DAF Museum in Eindhoven is a tribute to the renowned Dutch manufacturer, showcasing an array of trucks, rare production vehicles, and prototypes. Founded in 1928 by the Van Doornes brothers, the museum delves into the company's history and its evolution over time. Visitors can explore a reconstruction of the 1930s era, featuring the factory, office of the Van Doren brothers, neighboring shops, pub, and vintage garage.
name: DAF Museum

excerpt: Strijp-S is a neighborhood and former industrial park in the Eindhoven district of Strijp. The area belonged to electronics company Philips. Since 2000, creative companies and housing have been established in the former industrial buildings. Eindhoven Strijp-S railway station serves the district. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Strijp-S, located in the Eindhoven district of Strijp, was once an industrial park owned by Philips. Since 2000, it has transformed into a vibrant neighborhood with creative companies and residential spaces housed in former industrial buildings. The area is served by the Eindhoven Strijp-S railway station, making it easily accessible. This dynamic district showcases adaptive reuse of industrial structures and represents the city's future development.
name: Strijp-S

excerpt: Completed in 1867, this soaring neo-Gothic Catholic church features 2 towers & rose windows.
detail_description: St. Catherine's Church, also known as St. Catharinakerk, is a stunning Neo-Gothic Catholic church completed in 1867. The original structure was dedicated to St. Catherine of Alexandria and dates back to the 13th century but underwent severe damage from wars and fires over the years. Restored to its former glory, the current building incorporates symbolic references and features two towers representing the purity of Mary and the strength of David.
name: St. Catherine's Church

detail_description: De Blob in Eindhoven is a futuristic and eye-catching building made entirely of glass and steel, serving as the entrance to the famous Admirant Mall. This landmark symbolizes the city's modernity with its unique round shape and absence of defining walls or corners. Standing at 25 meters tall, it is a great example of Eindhoven's architectural innovation. Visitors can explore shops and cafes within the building while enjoying picturesque views of the city.
name: De Blob Eindhoven

detail_description: Bottle Distillery, located in Eindhoven, is a unique and fascinating distillery that produces handmade gin, rum, vodka, and various liqueurs. The tasting room and bar offer delicious drinks and fantastic food in a relaxed setting. Visitors can also take part in guided tours to learn about the production process of these alcoholic beverages. Housed in the last textile factory in Eindhoven, this family-run brewery aims to preserve history while staying current with its products.
name: Bottle Distillery

excerpt: Museum at PSV Eindhoven home ground, charting club history with trophies, photos & memorabilia.
detail_description: The PSV Museum, located at the home ground of PSV Eindhoven, offers a comprehensive look into the club's rich history through trophies, photos, and memorabilia. As one of Europe's most successful football franchises, the museum showcases historic outfits, artifacts, and multimedia displays highlighting career milestones. Visitors can immerse themselves in the world of PSV Eindhoven through interactive experiences and admire the club's greatest achievements.
name: PSV Museum

detail_description: PreHistorisch Dorp, also known as prehistoric village, is a unique theme park offering visitors an immersive experience of early human civilization. Located in Eindhoven, it serves as a museum dedicated to the rural history of the city by replicating villages from six different historical periods. Visitors can witness and participate in farm work, hunting techniques, and daily village life activities recreated by real people. The park also features dramatic presentations at different time slots and has an on-site eatery.
name: PreHistorisch Dorp

excerpt: Trendy food market featuring international cuisine & bars, plus indoor & outdoor seating.
detail_description: Downtown Gourmet Market is a trendy food market that offers a wide range of international cuisines and bars, along with both indoor and outdoor seating. It's a great spot for food enthusiasts looking to sample diverse dishes from around the world, reminiscent of street food experiences in Camden and Shoreditch. Whether you're craving Vietnamese pho and bao buns or Spanish tapas, this market has it all.
name: Down Town Gourmet Market

excerpt: Popular park featuring open grassy areas, paths that wind around ponds & a sculpture garden.
detail_description: Stadswandelpark, located a few kilometers south of Eindhoven's city center, is a popular urban park known for its open grassy areas, winding paths around ponds, and a charming sculpture garden. It offers tranquil spaces with plenty of benches and meadows for relaxation. The park features stunning landscaped gardens, spacious lawns, picturesque water features, and hidden pathways to explore between the trees.
name: Stadswandelpark

detail_description: Motion Imagination Experience is a small interactive museum located in Piazza mall. The staff is friendly and the activities are interesting, allowing visitors to interact with their surroundings. It offers various light installations, a 4D show, and more. Although it could have more potential with additional features, it's a fun place to spend about an hour taking part in the activities and capturing great photos. There's also a clean cafeteria available for visitors to enjoy.
name: Motion Experience

excerpt: Eindhoven is a city in the province of North Brabant in the south Netherlands. Known as a technology and design hub, itâ€™s the birthplace of Philips electronics, which built the Philips Stadium, home to the PSV soccer team. The Philips Museum traces the company's design history. Nearby, the Van Abbemuseum focuses on art and design. Northwest, the former industrial complex Strijp-S houses design shops and restaurants.
detail_description: Eindhoven, located in the southern Netherlands, is renowned as a center for technology and design. It is the birthplace of Philips electronics and home to the PSV soccer team's Philips Stadium. The city boasts attractions such as the Philips Museum, which showcases the company's design history, and the Van Abbemuseum, focusing on art and design. Additionally, Eindhoven features the innovative Strijp-S district with its design shops and restaurants.
name: Eindhoven

excerpt: Online collection of local art &  crafts, plus itinerant temporary installations around the city.
name: Eindhoven Museum

detail_description: Dutch Design Week is an annual event held in Eindhoven, known as the largest design event in Northern Europe. Lasting for nine days in October, it showcases works from hundreds of designers, focusing on future innovations and designs. The event features exhibitions, events, debates, and lectures at various locations throughout the city. It is recommended to rent a bike due to the spacious nature of the venues. Visitors are advised to plan for a five-day visit to fully experience everything on offer.
name: Dutch Design Week

detail_description: Park Theater Eindhoven is a popular cultural center in the heart of Eindhoven, Netherlands. It's known for its diverse range of performances and cultural experiences, making it a top attraction for both locals and tourists. The theater hosts impressive shows, including the Winter Christmas Circus and musicals like Mama Mia. Visitors can enjoy well-organized events with options for theater menus and complimentary drinks during intermissions. The venue offers good visibility of the stage, although some areas may have limited leg space.
name: Park Theater Eindhoven

excerpt: A 494-acre natural park with 2 museums, a swimming pool, ice skating rink, mini golf & restaurant.
detail_description: Genneper Parken is a sprawling 494-acre natural park that attracts over 3 million visitors annually. Nestled just outside the city's main ring road, this charming destination boasts picturesque landscapes, hidden ponds, and medieval architecture. The park offers a range of recreational activities including mini-golf, swimming pool access, and an inviting restaurant called Pavilion Genneper Parken set amidst lush greenery.
name: Genneper Parken

detail_description: Paviljoen Genneper Parken is a sprawling area located to the south of the city, offering a wide range of activities for visitors. It features hiking routes, an organic farm, one of Europe's largest indoor swimming complexes, and an ice-skating rink in winter. The park also boasts museums, a swimming pool, mini-golf facilities, and a restaurant amidst its natural beauty.
name: Paviljoen Genneper Parken

detail_description: Piet Hein Eek Green Restaurant offers a taste of local design at the workshop and showroom of Piet Hein Eek, a renowned Dutch designer. The sustainable approach to furniture and interiors reflects Eindhoven's commitment to conscious design. Visitors can enjoy a beautifully composed 4-course menu with a good price-quality ratio in a personal atmosphere with exceptional service. The tasting menu features fresh, high-quality ingredients showcasing the chef's care and attention in each course.
name: Piet Hein Eek Green Restaurant

excerpt: This children's outdoor play park includes a pirate-themed area, a shallow pool & a petting zoo.
detail_description: Speelpark de Splinter in Eindhoven is a massive outdoor playground that spans an area equivalent to seven football fields. It's a popular destination for families, offering a safe and enjoyable environment for kids to have the time of their lives. The park features various attractions including a pirate-themed area, shallow pools for toddlers and older children, slides, a castle, and even a petting zoo.
name: Speelpark de Splinter

excerpt: Vibrant passageway known for its robust collection of late-night pubs & cafes.
detail_description: Stratumseind is a lively and vibrant passageway in Eindhoven, known for its bustling collection of late-night pubs, cafes, and colorful neon lighting. It's considered the longest pub-street in the Netherlands, boasting over 40 bars and numerous dining options. This pedestrian area is also great for shopping and dining during the day. Visitors can explore this bustling street in the evening to experience its energetic nightlife scene.
name: Stratumseind

excerpt: Nuenen is a town in the municipality of Nuenen, Gerwen en Nederwetten in the Netherlands. From 1883 to 1885, Vincent van Gogh lived and worked in Nuenen. In 1944, a battle was fought there during Operation Market Garden. The local dialect is called Peellands. In 2009, Nuenen had a population of 22,437. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Nuenen, a town in the Netherlands, holds historical significance as the place where Vincent van Gogh lived and worked from 1883 to 1885. It was also the site of a battle during Operation Market Garden in 1944. The local dialect, known as Peellands, adds to its cultural charm.
name: Nuenen

excerpt: Compact shopping center in a converted factory, featuring local art, design & fashion boutiques.
detail_description: Urban Shopper Shopping Centre is a unique and compact shopping destination located in the creative Strijp-S area of The Netherlands. Housed in a converted Philips factory hall, it features a diverse range of local art, design, and fashion boutiques. The center embraces the concept store model, providing independent retailers with an affordable space to showcase their goods. Visitors can explore an array of original items including clothing, decorations, baby products, and Polish ceramics while supporting local entrepreneurs and industries.
name: Urban Shopper Shopping Centre

excerpt: Contemporary art gallery showcasing international & future talent in a former factory building.
detail_description: MU Hybrid Art House is a contemporary art gallery located in a former factory building in the Strijp-S district. It showcases international and future talent, featuring unique sculptures and other artwork created by young artists from around the world. The gallery transforms its exhibitions five to six times a year, ensuring that visitors always encounter new and captivating pieces. MU Hybrid Art House aims to redefine the boundaries of art, offering an immersive experience that goes beyond traditional perceptions of artistic expression.
name: MU Hybrid Art House
address: Torenallee 40-06, Entrance side: Ketelhuisplein, 5617 BA Eindhoven, Netherlands

detail_description: Indulge your inner child at Intelligentia ICE by Jeffrey, one of the top ice cream spots in Eindhoven. The vibrant pink interior and friendly staff create a whimsical atmosphere that feels like something out of a movie set or a commercial. But what sets this place apart is its unique ice cream flavors, such as Cuban cigar, marshmallow, and aniseed (The Drop). Using fruits, vegetables, and herbs, they craft these unconventional flavors that you won't find elsewhere.
name: Intelligentia ICE by Jeffrey

detail_description: Radio Royaal is a unique dining spot located in Eindhoven's Strijp-S quarter, housed in one of Philips' former factories. The restaurant offers not only delicious food but also an industrial and rustic ambiance. With high ceilings, brick walls, and stylish interiors, the place exudes a lively atmosphere. Inspired by French cuisine with a modern twist, the menu features artfully presented dishes.
name: Radio Royaal

detail_description: GLOW Festival - Caleidoscope (Temporary) is an enchanting event featuring 25 portals, with 24 scattered throughout Eindhoven's city center and one at the airport. Each portal narrates a unique story envisioned by artist Valerio Festi. The gates exude an Indian, Bollywood-inspired ambiance and come alive after dark, casting a warm and inviting glow as you wander through the heart of Eindhoven.
name: GLOW Festival - Caleidoscope (Temporary)

detail_description: Foundation Lichtjesroute is an annual festival in Eindhoven that commemorates the city's liberation from the German Reich during World War II. The event, which takes place in September, features a parade and various light ornaments along the Route of Lights. Volunteers work tirelessly to set up and dismantle the decorations each year. Participants can enjoy a lively atmosphere with refreshments while cycling through the illuminated city streets.
name: Foundation Lichtjesroute

excerpt: Indoor & outdoor exhibits documenting Van Gogh's life & the local landmarks he painted.
detail_description: The Van Gogh Village Museum, located in the picturesque village of Nuenen just a short drive from Eindhoven, offers both indoor and outdoor exhibits that provide insight into Vincent Van Gogh's life and the local landmarks he painted. The museum includes the completely restored pastor's house where Van Gogh lived for two years, along with 20 other preserved historic buildings.
name: Van Gogh Village Museum

detail_description: Area 51 is a popular indoor skate park located in Strijp-S, Eindhoven. It features impressive ramps and hosts events that attract visitors from various places. The park offers challenges suitable for all skill levels and has a cafe/bar on-site, as well as equipment hire and a reception shop. The facility is well-organized with ample space, clean amenities, and seating areas. Additionally, there are smaller ramps and rails available for less experienced riders to practice safely before attempting the larger courses.
name: Area 51

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Eindhoven, Phood Kitchen is a pioneering vegan-friendly restaurant that beautifully marries sustainability with culinary creativity. Housed in a former dairy boiler room, this spacious eatery features high ceilings and indoor trees that evoke an inviting outdoor ambiance. The standout element is its unique aquaponic farm located just below the dining area, where fresh salad greens and shiitake mushrooms are cultivated right on-site.
name: Phood Kitchen
address: Hugo van der Goeslaan 2-01, 5613 LG Eindhoven, Netherlands

detail_description: Coffeelab is a popular coffee spot located conveniently at the central station in Eindhoven. It's not just a place for great coffee, but also offers a cozy atmosphere for flex-working, mingling with fellow coffee enthusiasts, or enjoying a refreshing coffee tonic in the sun outside. The interior is adorned with stylish furniture and lush greenery, creating an inviting ambiance. The cafe takes pride in serving homemade vegan cakes, sandwiches, and other delectable treats.
name: Coffeelab

detail_description: When you find yourself in Eindhoven, a visit to VANE Skybar is an absolute must. Perched atop the NH Collection Eindhoven Centre hotel, this stylish bar offers not only a vibrant atmosphere but also breathtaking views of the city and beyond. Inspired by local weathervanes, each cocktail at VANE is a unique creation made from homemade ingredients that reflect various directions of the wind compass, taking guests on an exciting journey through diverse flavors and textures.
name: VANE Skybar Bar

detail_description: COFFEELAB Strijp-S is a pioneering coffee shop in Eindhoven that aims to create engaging interactions and unique coffee experiences for its customers. The co-owner, Jeroen Veldkamp, introduced some distinctive flavors for visitors to try. Additionally, the establishment caters to gluten allergies and offers a worry-free dining experience. With two outlets in the city, COFFEELAB Strijp-S exudes urban vibes and serves excellent coffee and baked goods from their own lab.
name: COFFEELAB Strijp-S

detail_description: Can Gallery -Graffiti/Street art/Workshop- in Eindhoven is a must-visit for street art enthusiasts. The area boasts stunning graffiti, murals, and other captivating works. Strijp and De Berenkuil are popular spots to explore the vibrant street art scene. Visitors can opt for personalized street tours to fully immerse themselves in the experience.
name: Can Gallery -Graffiti/Street art/Workshop-

detail_description: The FeelGood Market in Eindhoven is a vibrant monthly gathering that brings together locals and visitors to enjoy a diverse range of handmade goods, organic food, and live music. The market showcases an array of products including clothing, jewelry, art, and gadgets while offering a lively atmosphere with enjoyable live music. It's also a great place to indulge in various snacks and refreshing drinks. Located in Strijp S, the market offers beautiful products and new concepts for visitors to explore.
name: Feelgood market Eindhoven

detail_description: Strijp-S is a vibrant neighborhood in Eindhoven that has transformed from its industrial roots as a former Philips electronics park into a lively hub of activity. This area boasts an inviting atmosphere, perfect for enjoying coffee or grabbing a bite to eat at one of the many cozy spots scattered throughout. The beautifully renovated spaces create an open and welcoming environment, making it an ideal destination for both locals and visitors alike.
name: Strijp-S

excerpt: Stretching from residential areas to the airport, Strijp is anchored by the modern Philips Stadium, home of PSV Eindhoven soccer club. Fans can watch the team train at De Herdgang complex, on the edge of leafy Philips de Jongh park. Looming above a busy intersection, the Hovenring is an elevated roundabout for cyclists, while a 1960s building resembling a UFO houses the Evoluon conference center.
detail_description: Strijp, located in Eindhoven, is a vibrant area that stretches from residential neighborhoods to the airport. It is home to the modern Philips Stadium where fans can catch PSV Eindhoven soccer club in action. The De Herdgang complex offers a chance to watch the team train, set on the edge of the picturesque Philips de Jongh park. One of its unique features is the Hovenring, an elevated roundabout designed for cyclists.
name: Strijp

detail_description: TAC Studios is a lively cultural hub located in the heart of Eindhoven, Netherlands. It offers a diverse range of contemporary art and cultural experiences, making it a vibrant and dynamic destination for visitors. As one of the top attractions in the city, TAC provides an esteemed platform for artists and creators to showcase their work, creating an inspiring environment that captivates the imagination and sparks creativity.
name: TAC Studios

detail_description: Everybody Relax is a massage and relaxation center located in Eindhoven, one of the greenest cities in the Netherlands. The city offers a picturesque setting for leisurely strolls along the River Dommel, with Stadswandelpark serving as an outdoor art gallery adorned with modern sculptures. Clients have praised Martyna's expertise at Everybody Relax, particularly highlighting her deep tissue massages and Kobido face massages.
name: Everybody Relax massage praktijk

excerpt: Unique roadside art installation depicting large bowling pins being struck by bowling ball.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant city of Eindhoven, the Flying Pins Monument is a whimsical roadside art installation that captures the playful spirit of bowling. This striking piece features oversized yellow bowling pins being dramatically knocked down by a giant bowling ball, creating an eye-catching spectacle for both locals and travelers alike. Designed by renowned artists Claes Oldenburg and Coosje van Bruggen, this 8.
name: Flying Pins
address: John F Kennedylaan 2, 5612 AB Eindhoven, Netherlands

excerpt: Energetic venue offering 14 taps, home-brewed beers & hearty eats, plus a terrace with river views.
detail_description: CafÃ© 100 Watt is a vibrant venue located in Eindhoven, Netherlands. It houses the taproom of Stadsbrouwerij Eindhoven, the city's largest working brewery, set in a former carpet factory by the River Dommel. The modern hangout features a stylishly minimalist interior with ample natural light streaming through large windows. Guests can enjoy river views from the spacious terrace or opt for a more intimate experience on the courtyard terrace.
name: CafÃ© 100 Watt

detail_description: The National Swimming Center the Tongelreep in Eindhoven, Netherlands is a world-class aquatic facility that has been instrumental in training Olympic swimmers. It offers swimming lessons for all ages and skill levels, with dedicated and patient instructors. The center features a beautiful 10-lane 50-meter pool and an 8-lane 25-meter pool, making it suitable for both recreational activities and competitive events.
name: National Swimming Center the Tongelreep

excerpt: Modernised 1910 venue & current home of PSV Eindhoven, with a capacity of 35,000 spectators
detail_description: The Philips Stadium, home to the PSV Eindhoven football club, is a modernized venue with a capacity of 35,000 spectators. It holds historical significance as it marks the original spot where the team first played in 1913. Visitors can catch a match for an unforgettable experience and join in cheering on PSV with the home supporters. The stadium offers a great atmosphere and delicious food and drinks, although they may be pricey.
name: Philips Stadium

excerpt: Furniture design studio housing contemporary art gallery, with temporary displays by Dutch artists.
detail_description: Piet Hein Eek is a multifaceted space located in a former Philips factory in Eindhoven, housing a furniture design studio, contemporary art gallery, and a restaurant. The venue offers visitors the opportunity to explore the workshop and showroom of designer Piet Hein Eek, as well as enjoy a meal at the Lobby Restaurant and Grand Cafe. The restaurant serves fresh, organic dishes made with hyperlocal ingredients by Chef Erling.
name: Piet Hein Eek

excerpt: Conference center in a landmark 1960s former science museum building that resembles a UFO.
detail_description: The Next Nature Museum, housed in a striking UFO-shaped building known as the Evoluon, offers an immersive experience for visitors of all ages. The museum features interactive displays on technology, space farming, and the future, including opportunities to engage with VR technology. Originally built as a science museum by Phillips in 1966, the building now serves as a conference center and exhibition space. Visitors can explore its unique architecture and enjoy refreshments while taking in the RetroFuture exhibition showcasing images of the future.
name: Next Nature Museum

excerpt: Casino featuring table games like roulette & blackjack, plus slot machines & a restaurant.
detail_description: Holland Casino Eindhoven is a cozy casino located in the heart of Eindhoven, offering a range of table games such as roulette and blackjack, as well as an array of slot machines. Situated within the De Heuvel shopping center, this casino provides not only gaming entertainment but also a dining experience. The restaurant offers a carefully crafted menu with daily specials, providing delicious and fresh meals in an amply decorated and luxurious space.
name: Holland Casino Eindhoven
address: Winkelcentrum Heuvel, Ten Hagestraat 6A, 5611 EG Eindhoven, Netherlands

detail_description: Muziekgebouw Frits Philips is a gem nestled in the heart of Eindhoven, offering an exceptional musical experience that captivates both locals and visitors alike. The venue boasts remarkable acoustics, making it an ideal setting for performances ranging from classical masterpieces to contemporary orchestral works. Attendees have raved about the outstanding talent showcased here, including memorable renditions of Schumann and Brahms by talented quartets like Benjamin Grosvenor's ensemble.
name: Muziekgebouw Frits Philips

excerpt: Country's largest falconry centre on 2.5. hectares with birds of prey demonstrations & raptor shows.
name: Falconcrest Birds of Prey Park
